<cite class="citation book" about="#mwt244" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book\n","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"last1":{"wt":"Haase"},"first1":{"wt":"Hugo"},"author-link1":{"wt":"Hugo Haase"},"chapter":{"wt":"The Debate in the Reichstag on Internal Political Conditions, April 5–6, 1916"},"editor1-last":{"wt":"Lutz"},"editor1-first":{"wt":"Ralph Haswell"},"title":{"wt":"Fall of the German Empire, 1914–1918"},"chapter-url":{"wt":"https://books.google.com/books?id=cW6mAAAAIAAJ"},"series":{"wt":"Hoover War Library publications"},"issue":{"wt":"1–2"},"publisher":{"wt":"Stanford University Press"},"publication-date":{"wt":"1932"},"page":{"wt":"233"},"isbn":{"wt":"9780804723800"},"accessdate":{"wt":"2015-08-25"},"quote":{"wt":"Gentlemen, when it comes time to formulate peace conditions, it is time to think of another thing than war aims."},"year":{"wt":"1932"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBHQ"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Hugo_Haase" title="Hugo Haase" id="mwBHU">Haase, Hugo</a> (1932). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=cW6mAAAAIAAJ" id="mwBHY">"The Debate in the Reichstag on Internal Political Conditions, April 5–6, 1916"</a>.  In Lutz, Ralph Haswell. <i id="mwBHc">Fall of the German Empire, 1914–1918</i>. Hoover War Library publications. Stanford University Press. p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwBHg"> </span>233. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwBHk">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwBHo"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/9780804723800" title="Special:BookSources/9780804723800" id="mwBHs">9780804723800</a><span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwBHw">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwBH0">2015-08-25</span></span>. <q id="mwBH4">Gentlemen, when it comes time to formulate peace conditions, it is time to think of another thing than war aims.</q></cite><span title="c